 Such a shift towards a per plane tax would reap the above-mentioned potential
 efficiency gains by increasing load factors und leading to the use of larger
 airplanes.
 The UK might have expected that if they were to move ahead and implement
 the tax change, other countries would oppose it.
 Such opposition did indeed materialize when the EU included all flights
