al flights after one year.
 The opposition by many countries against the taxation of international
 flights might cause the low level of taxes mainly through its workings
 `off the equilibrium path' by preventing countries from even considering
 such reforms.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Ticket taxes seem not to be subject to these legal obstacles.
 The question therefore arises as to why ticket taxes are so low today.
 As mentioned above, Keen, Strand (2006) suggest that this might be due
